A street brawl by hoodlums of Adeta and Isale-Jagun areas of Ilorin, Kwara state capital, has left many injured. The fight reportedly started on Sunday night and continued till yesterday morning, it was learnt.   Police arrest three men for gang-rape     Gunmen kill two policemen in Anambra     How APC’s planned February 26 convention was scuttled   The rampaging hoodlums freely used guns, broken bottles and machetes, attacking people and  smashing car windows, The Nation was told. Many people sustained injuries during the attack. Police confirmed the incident, saying three persons have been arrested.